Installation of React:

create-react-app : Recommended tool for creating react projects which is published by Facebook

1. npm install -g create-react-app  ( -g is used to install globally)
2. create-react-app <name-of-the-project> --scripts-version 1.1.5
* --scripts-version 1.1.5 : It just impacts the structure of the project but doesnot change the react scripts
3.Once installed, you will find a bunch of commands
npm start: starts the development server
npm build: Builds the app in to static files for production
npm test: Starts the test runner
npm eject: Removes this tool and copies build dependencies, configuration files and scripts into the app directory. If you do this, you cant go back.